{
  "title": "Setting Up PDF Template in SiteFlow",
  "metaTitle": "Setting Up PDF Template in SiteFlow",
  "metaDescription": "Set up a PDF template in SiteFlow — choose the default layout or upload a custom branded header and footer for all POs, invoices, GRNs, quotations, and reports.",
  "canonical": "https://siteflow.com/help/settings-configuration/how-to-set-up-pdf-template/",
  "slug": "settings-configuration/how-to-set-up-pdf-template",
  "category": "settings-configuration",
  "type": "help",
  "author": "SiteFlow Operations Team",
  "publishDate": "2026-05-08T19:18:15+00:00",
  "body": "\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-8169739fa0bdca00db3aa7a5ef203e89 wp-block-paragraph\">How to choose between the default SiteFlow PDF template and a custom template using your own header and footer images. The PDF template controls how all downloaded documents and reports appear, including Purchase Orders, Sales Invoices, GRNs, Quotations, and Reports.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-8b579f97c281b6a0e88fc50ff4c2bc9b\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-f149dcfed745e188099564eb044f8ecf\">\n<li>You need Admin access</li>\n<li>If you want to use a custom template, prepare your header and footer images before starting. See the image specifications in Step 3 below.</li>\n<li class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-70bb618db4890e0269c71c562e2722fe\">Make sure your Company Details are up to date (name, address, GST, logo) before setting up the template. The default SiteFlow template pulls from Company Details automatically.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-446807853f25a8805c6ca3afb17c1048\">Step 1: Go to Settings</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-af211e30a7d126690952b419306821e5 wp-block-paragraph\">Click Setting in the left sidebar.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-9b704a37897522e6fe6effc37f1e397a\">Step 2: Open PDF Template</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-6054131f447e4c339c5a69aea92a24c4 wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>PDF Template</strong> from the Settings menu.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-f86f00a26f3c140602e07c8109e9fb6c wp-block-paragraph\">You will see two template options.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-6cb9e1f133492a9bfeac822ae573e161\">Step 3: Choose Your Template</h2>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Option A — Default SiteFlow Template</h3>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-2823e2c678d339abcc540437f4643081 wp-block-paragraph\">Select <strong>SiteFlow Template</strong> to use the standard SiteFlow PDF layout.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-f3dbddf3f6b46682af37c1b59d8875f3 wp-block-paragraph\">The default template automatically includes:</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Element</th><th>Where It Comes From</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Company name</td><td>Company Details settings</td></tr><tr><td>Company logo</td><td>Uploaded in Company Details</td></tr><tr><td>Company address and GST number</td><td>Company Details settings</td></tr><tr><td>Signature and stamp</td><td>Uploaded in Company Details</td></tr><tr><td>Document title (e.g. Purchase Order, Tax Invoice)</td><td>Generated automatically by SiteFlow</td></tr><tr><td>Document data (line items, amounts, dates, parties)</td><td>Pulled from the document itself</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-2a907eeca03fbfba610d3a114c96f7bc wp-block-paragraph\">This template is ready to use as soon as Company Details are filled in. No image uploads are needed.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-4b1ea63dc5611f2e759c1396024319a8 wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Use the default template when:</strong> your team needs a clean, professional document layout immediately without designing custom branding.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Option B — Custom Template</h3>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-971ea6221ecde27b9a9d4b4c2c657ff7 wp-block-paragraph\">Select <strong>Custom Template</strong> to replace the standard header and footer with your own branded images.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-48bddf123752c898dbcc2e748bc1aa51 wp-block-paragraph\">This is useful when:</p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-2f0f7157a6f7e287a33ab8d2c9b210c9\">\n<li>Your company has a standard letterhead design you want on all documents</li>\n<li>You want to include your company’s branding, address layout, or compliance text in the header</li>\n<li>You want to include bank details, authorised signatory text, or terms in the footer</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Upload Header Image</h4>\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-4b3b8edda8ba685e33a4b6c05396954f\">\n<li>Click <strong>Upload Header Image</strong></li>\n<li>Select your image file from your device</li>\n<li>The image uploads and previews on screen</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-b8e7be10ba953cccef6f7cb8ca9938ac wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Header image specifications:</strong></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Specification</th><th>Requirement</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dimensions</td><td>794 x 120 pixels exactly</td></tr><tr><td>File format</td><td>JPG or PNG</td></tr><tr><td>Content to include</td><td>Company name, logo, address, GST number, phone number</td></tr><tr><td>Content to avoid</td><td>Do not include document titles (e.g. “Purchase Order”) in the header image. SiteFlow adds the document title automatically below the header.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Upload Footer Image</h4>\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-d682822d2fc9a2753c219a29b6e8b6b9\">\n<li>Click <strong>Upload Footer Image</strong></li>\n<li>Select your image file from your device</li>\n<li>The image uploads and previews on screen</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-3cc5d307c7e665d511cbfe0ab143cad6 wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Footer image specifications:</strong></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Specification</th><th>Requirement</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dimensions</td><td>794 x 80 pixels exactly</td></tr><tr><td>File format</td><td>JPG or PNG</td></tr><tr><td>Content to include</td><td>Bank details, authorised signatory, company registration number, disclaimer text</td></tr><tr><td>Content to avoid</td><td>Do not repeat information already in the header</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-3f79ff71e557e10eb78f586e79faee4f\">Step 4: Save</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-28af084e90ee12ca7ed8995646620182 wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply the template.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-f72e6eafc7df83099588731b1405cf61 wp-block-paragraph\">The selected template applies immediately to all new PDFs generated from the app. Existing downloaded PDFs are not affected.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Which Documents Use This Template</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-2a252b823ee0a9e7280f9f5633a2716f wp-block-paragraph\">The PDF template applies to all downloadable documents in SiteFlow, including:</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Document</th><th>Where to Download</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Purchase Order</td><td>Procurement section, Download icon on each PO</td></tr><tr><td>Sales Invoice</td><td>Project Estimate, Invoices tab, View then Download</td></tr><tr><td>Quotation</td><td>CRM Quotations, Download option</td></tr><tr><td>GRN (Goods Received Note)</td><td>Material tab, on each GRN entry</td></tr><tr><td>Subcontractor Work Order</td><td>Subcon Work Orders, Download option</td></tr><tr><td>Reports</td><td>Reports section, Download icon on any report</td></tr><tr><td>Daily Progress Report</td><td>Reports section, DPR Download</td></tr><tr><td>Attendance and Salary Report</td><td>Reports section</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">How to Design the Header Image</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-82ba85772f14246ef9719b40b94dfcd6 wp-block-paragraph\">If you are creating the header image for the first time, use these guidelines:</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-710fa61d3f6dbb0bb85de45ef4178bb0 wp-block-paragraph\">The canvas must be exactly <strong>794 x 120 pixels</strong>. At 72 DPI, this is approximately 28 cm wide and 4.2 cm tall.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-9e78ae970cd37f1f64d7548d929b0a9c wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Recommended layout (left to right):</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-ca04fff4ddfb5c1cec57b31e69d51a12\">\n<li>Left section: Company logo</li>\n<li>Centre section: Company name in large text, address and GST below in smaller text</li>\n<li>Right section: Phone number, email, website</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-15eee16b76e3199c93729a90c902cee9 wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Design tools that work well:</strong> Canva, Adobe Illustrator, Microsoft PowerPoint (export as PNG at 100% size), Photoshop.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-6e36fb2b56fa836a0fb446efff44f609 wp-block-paragraph\">Export the image as PNG for the best quality on printed documents.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">How to Design the Footer Image</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-a18338131a4d301775c70518c9d7a4a2 wp-block-paragraph\">The footer canvas must be exactly <strong>794 x 80 pixels</strong>.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-35d5427f88b0d0a86476eb26f5546027 wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Recommended content:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-81a496df5e54e8e52e79e216b2db3ab2\">\n<li>Bank name, account number, IFSC code, branch name</li>\n<li>“Authorised Signatory” label with space for signature</li>\n<li>Company registration number or CIN if required</li>\n<li>Any standard disclaimer text your company uses on documents</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-3f32cf6020ebf3d6a891c2fc9d47c10d wp-block-paragraph\">Keep text size at minimum 10pt equivalent at 72 DPI to ensure it is readable when printed.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Tips</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-da505cd66093a8c06025116ced9a736c\">\n<li>Use exactly the specified dimensions. Images that are even slightly off may appear stretched, compressed, or cut off on the PDF.</li>\n<li>PNG format preserves text sharpness better than JPG, especially for small fonts and fine lines in a footer.</li>\n<li>After saving, download a test document (such as a Purchase Order or Sales Invoice) to review how the header and footer appear before sharing with clients or vendors.</li>\n<li>You can switch between the default SiteFlow template and a custom template at any time by returning to PDF Template settings and clicking Save again.</li>\n<li>Custom fields added to document types (via Custom Fields settings) will appear in the document body between the header and footer, not inside the header or footer images.</li>\n<li>The watermark and signature uploaded in Company Details appear on documents regardless of which template is selected.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-9db1dda5d3fc91a1c692d196a0c587df\">If Something Goes Wrong</h2>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"></h2>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Problem</th><th>Likely Cause</th><th>What to Do</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Cannot see PDF Template option</td><td>Not an Admin</td><td>Ask your Admin to configure the template or grant Admin access</td></tr><tr><td>Header or footer image looks stretched or distorted on PDF</td><td>Wrong image dimensions</td><td>Resize the image to exactly 794 x 120 px (header) or 794 x 80 px (footer) and re-upload</td></tr><tr><td>Template not applying to new documents</td><td>Setting not saved</td><td>Return to PDF Template settings, confirm the correct option is selected, and click Save</td></tr><tr><td>Uploaded image not showing after upload</td><td>Unsupported file format</td><td>Use JPG or PNG only. Convert from other formats (WEBP, SVG, BMP) before uploading</td></tr><tr><td>Company name or logo not appearing on default template</td><td>Company Details not filled in</td><td>Go to Settings, open Company Details, and upload the logo and fill in the company name and address</td></tr><tr><td>Header text is too small to read on printed document</td><td>Font size too small in the image</td><td>Recreate the header image with larger text. Minimum 10pt equivalent at 72 DPI is recommended</td></tr><tr><td>Need to remove the custom template and go back to default</td><td>Easy to revert</td><td>Go to PDF Template settings, select SiteFlow Template, and click Save</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n"
}